@page "/faq"

<PageTitle>FAQ – EventPrime</PageTitle>

<!-- Page Banner -->
<section class="page-banner">
    <div class="banner-shapes">
        <div class="banner-shape bs-1"></div>
        <div class="banner-shape bs-2"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container banner-body">
        <div class="section-tag">Help Center</div>
        <h1 class="banner-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="banner-subtitle">Everything you need to know about EventPrime. Can't find your answer? <a href="/contact" class="banner-link">Contact us.</a></p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ Section -->
<section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="faq-layout">

            <!-- Category Sidebar -->
            <aside class="faq-categories">
                <h3 class="cat-heading">Categories</h3>
                <ul class="cat-list">
                    <li class="cat-item active">🎟️ Tickets &amp; Booking</li>
                    <li class="cat-item">🗓️ Event Management</li>
                    <li class="cat-item">💳 Payments &amp; Refunds</li>
                    <li class="cat-item">🔒 Account &amp; Security</li>
                    <li class="cat-item">🤝 Partnerships</li>
                </ul>
            </aside>

            <!-- FAQ Items -->
            <div class="faq-items">

                <h2 class="faq-group-title">🎟️ Tickets &amp; Booking</h2>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">How do I purchase tickets for an event?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Browse to the event page and click <strong>Get Tickets</strong>. Choose your ticket type, quantity, and proceed to checkout. You'll receive an e-ticket via email shortly after payment is confirmed.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">Can I transfer my ticket to someone else?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! Log into your account, go to <strong>My Tickets</strong>, and select the ticket you want to transfer. Enter the recipient's email address and confirm. The transfer is instant.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">Are tickets available at the door?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>This depends on the event organizer. Most events sell tickets exclusively through EventPrime to avoid sellouts. We recommend purchasing in advance as popular events often sell out quickly.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">What if I lost my ticket confirmation email?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>No worries! Log into your EventPrime account and navigate to <strong>My Tickets</strong>. You can download or resend your ticket from there at any time.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <h2 class="faq-group-title">💳 Payments &amp; Refunds</h2>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">What payment methods are accepted?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We accept all major credit and debit cards (Visa, Mastercard, Amex), PayPal, Apple Pay, and Google Pay. All transactions are secured with industry-standard encryption.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">What is the refund policy?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Refund policies vary by event organizer. Generally, refund requests must be submitted at least 7 days before the event. If an event is cancelled by the organizer, you will receive a full refund automatically within 5–10 business days.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">Are there any booking fees?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>A small service fee may be applied depending on the event. This fee covers platform operations, secure payment processing, and customer support. The full cost including any fees is displayed before you confirm your purchase.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <h2 class="faq-group-title">🔒 Account &amp; Security</h2>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">How do I create an EventPrime account?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Click <strong>Sign Up</strong> in the top navigation, enter your name, email, and a strong password. You'll receive a verification email — click the link to activate your account and you're all set!</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">Is my personal data safe with EventPrime?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely. We take data privacy seriously. Your data is encrypted at rest and in transit. We never sell personal information to third parties. Please review our <a href="#" class="faq-link">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">How do I reset my password?</summary>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>On the login page, click <strong>Forgot Password?</strong> and enter your registered email address. You'll receive a reset link within a few minutes. The link expires after 30 minutes for security reasons.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Still Have Questions CTA -->
<section class="faq-cta">
    <div class="container faq-cta-inner">
        <span class="faq-cta-icon">🤔</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="faq-cta-title">Still have questions?</h3>
            <p class="faq-cta-sub">Our support team is ready to help you out.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-faq-contact">Contact Support →</a>
    </div>
</section>
